value.value: The mutation of either a splice site or stop codon that leads to an extended transcript.
The mutation of either a splice site or stop codon that leads to a truncated transcript.
A change in the nucleotide sequence of a region between gene loci.
A mutation occurring in a sequence that regulates non-sense mediated mRNA decay.
A change in the nucleotide sequence of a non-coding gene.
A change in the nucleotide sequence of an exon in a non-coding gene.
A change in the nucleotide sequence of a regulatory region for a gene.
A deletion mutation where the deleted sequence includes a regulatory region for a gene.
An increase in the copy number of a region containing a regulatory sequence for a gene.

A mutation occurring within the start codon of a gene that results in a sequence that no longer encodes a start codon. This can result in a gene deletion or gene transcription may start from an alternative start site.

value.value: A water-insoluble camptothecin derivative.  Aminocamptothecin binds to the nuclear enzyme topoisomerase I, thereby inhibiting repair of single-strand DNA breakages.  Because the terminal lactone ring of aminocamptothecin required for the agent's antitumor activity spontaneously opens under physiological conditions to an inactive carboxy form, the drug must be administered over an extended period of time to achieve effective cytotoxicity. (NCI04)

value.value: The recombinant analogue of an endogenous cytokine interleukin 13 with potential antineoplastic activity. Produced by lymphocytes and exhibiting a variety of functions, interleukin-13 (therapeutic) inhibits DNA synthesis and regulates inflammatory and immune responses. In animal models, this agent has been shown to kill tumor cells both directly and indirectly by activating the host immune system at the tumor site. (NCI04)
